snippet: Property developers in China are struggling to unload unsold units as potential buyers try to decide if prices will continue to fall.
abstract: China's property market is under intense pressure, with prices for new housing falling 1 percent to 9 percent in few months in 70 mainland cities; many possible buyers are mulling whether prices will continue to drop; weak real estate prices are big challenge for government as it attempts to manage economic weakness.

byline.contributor: Hilda Wang, Jonah Kessel and Neil Gough contributed reporting.

lead_paragraph: Property developers in China are struggling to unload unsold units as potential buyers try to decide if prices will continue to fall.

headline.main: China’s Housing Resists Efforts to Spur Market
headline.print_headline: China’s Housing Resists Efforts to Spur Market
